feld Stadium]], [[Pretoria]], South Africa || {{fb|CMR}}\n| style=text-align:center | 1\u20131\n| style=text-align:center | 2\u20131 || [[2010 FIFA World Cup Group E|2010 FIFA World Cup]]\n|-\n! scope=row | 13\n| rowspan=2 style=text-align:center | 41\n| rowspan=2 | 6 September 2011\n| rowspan=2 | Parken Stadium, Copenhagen, Denmark\n| rowspan=2 | {{fb|NOR}}\n| style=text-align:center | 1\u20130\n| rowspan=2 style=text-align:center | 2\u20130 \n| rowspan=2 | [[UEFA Euro 2012 qualifying Group H|UEFA Euro 2012 qualification]]\n|-\n! scope=row | 14\n| style=text-align:center | 2\u20130\n|-\n! scope=row | 15\n| style=text-align:center | 43\n| 11 October 2011 || Parken Stadium, Copenhagen, Denmark || {{fb|POR}}\n| style=text-align:center | 2\u20130\n| style=text-align:center | 2\u20131 || UEFA Euro 2012 qualification\n|-\n! scope=row | 16\n| style=text-align:center | 44\n| 11 November 2011 || Parken Stadium, Copenhagen, Denmark || {{fb|SWE}}\n| style=text-align:center | 1\u20130\n| style=text-align:center | 2\u20130 || Friendly\n|-\n! scope=row | 17\n| style=text-align:center | 45\n| 15 November 2011 || [[Blue Water Arena]], [[Esbjerg]], Denmark || {{fb|FIN}}\n| style=text-align:center | 2\u20131\n| style=text-align:center | 2\u20131 || Friendly\n|-\n! scope=row | 18\n| style=text-align:center | 47\n| 26 May 2012 || [[Imtech Arena]], [[Hamburg]], Germany || {{fb|BRA}}\n| style=text-align:center | 1\u20133\n| style=text-align:center | 1\u20133 ||Friendly\n|-\n! scope=row | 19\n| rowspan=2 style=text-align:center | 50\n| rowspan=2 | 13 June 2012\n| rowspan=2 | [[Arena Lviv]], [[Lviv]], Ukraine\n| rowspan=2 | {{fb|POR}}\n| style=text-align:center | 1\u20132\n| rowspan=2 style=text-align:center | 2\u20133\n| rowspan=2 | [[UEFA Euro 2012 Group B|UEFA Euro 2012]]\n|-\n! scope=row | 20\n| style=text-align:center | 2\u20132\n|-\n! scope=row | 21\n| style=text-align:center | 53\n| 12 October 2012 || [[Vasil Levski National Stadium]], [[Sofia]], Bulgaria || {{fb|BUL}}\n| style=tex